 ."]},{"name":"Coggin","meanings":["English: variant of   Cogan  ."]},{"name":"Cohen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hyman, Meyer, Isadore, Emanuel, Moshe, Shlomo, Myer, Avi, Yehuda, Chaim.","Jewish: from Hebrew <i>kohen</i> ‘priest’. Priests are traditionally regarded as members of a hereditary caste descended from Aaron, brother of Moses. See also   Kaplan  .","Irish (Galway and Sligo): variant of   Coyne  ."]},{"name":"Coggins","meanings":["English: variant of   Cogan  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Coggan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Brigid, Conal, Seamus.  Jewish Hyman.","English: variant of   Cogan  .","Americanized form of Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic) <b>Kogan</b>, from the Russian pronunciation of   Cohen  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John De Cogan was born in 1087, his father, John de Cogan, was 37 and his mother, Basile de Ridelsford, was 22. He had at least 1 son with Hawise De Fitzwalter."},"et":{"1087–":"1087–Surnud","1087–Male":"1087–Surnud","1087–1135":"1087–1135","1105–1182":"1105–1182","1050–1110":"1050–1110","1065–1137":"1065–1137","1105":"1105","1137":"1137","1135":"1135","1110":"1110","1087":"1087","1065":"1065","1050":"1050","1182":"1182","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1087–":"1087–Kuollut","1087–Male":"1087–Kuollut","1087–1135":"1087–1135","1105–1182":"1105–1182","1050–1110":"1050–1110","1065–1137":"1065–1137","1105":"1105","1137":"1137","1135":"1135","1110":"1110","1087":"1087","1065":"1065","1050":"1050","1182":"1182","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1087–":"1087–Décédé","1087–Male":"1087–Décédé","1087–1135":"1087–1135","1105–1182":"1105–1182","1050–1110":"1050–1110","1065–1137":"1065–1137","1105":"1105","1137":"1137","1135":"1135","1110":"1110","1087":"1087","1065":"1065","1050":"1050","1182"